<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Zottman-Preacher-Curl"><strong>Dumbbell Zottman Preacher Curl</strong></h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-zottman-preacher-curl" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Dumbbell Zottman preacher curls</a> use the same dumbbell preacher curl movement described above but with a slight difference. Instead of bringing both arms back down with the same hand position, you add a wrist rotation. The opposite wrist position changes the muscle activation, giving you a great alternative isolation exercise.</p>



<p>The primary movers are the biceps short head and biceps long head. Secondary movers include the brachialis, brachioradialis, wrist flexors, and wrist extensors.&nbsp;</p>



<p>By rotating your wrists, you bring your arms down in a pronated position, palms facing down. This better targets the brachialis in the second phase and adds an additional grip challenge, improving grip strength.</p>



