<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>How To Do</strong></h4>



<ol>
<li>Adjust the preacher bench seat so your chest is level with the pad when you sit down.</li>



<li>Grab a pair of dumbbells and keep them by your sides. Your arms should be extended with your palms facing inwards.</li>



<li>Sit on the seat while bringing your arms onto the preacher bench. Shuffle forward until your chest is against the bench, extending your arms in front of you. Your upper arms should be against the pad.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Exhale and curl the dumbbells up to shoulder height. Use a supinated grip, palms facing up.</li>



<li>When you reach the top position, hold it briefly. Rotate your wrists until your palms are pronated, palms facing down.</li>



<li>Inhale and bring the dumbbell back to the starting position while using a pronated grip.</li>



<li>At the starting position, rotate your wrists back so your palms face up.</li>



<li>Repeat as needed.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Tips</strong>&nbsp;</h4>



<ul>
<li>Make sure you perform the wrist rotations using a slow and controlled movement. This limits potential wrist strain.</li>



<li>Donâ€™t move your elbows and arms as you rotate your wrists. Everything else should stay in the same position.</li>
</ul>



