<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Cable-Preacher-Curl"><strong>Cable Preacher Curl</strong></h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/cable-preacher-curl" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Cable preacher curls</a> take the normal preacher curl movement but perform it with a cable machine. The primary mover is your biceps short head. The secondary movers are your biceps long head, brachialis, and wrist flexors.</p>



<p>What&#8217;s great about this exercise is the multiple benefits of one movement. The cable machine provides constant resistance through the full range of motion. Meanwhile, the preacher bench reduces potential shoulder involvement, providing bicep isolation.</p>



<p>This gives you a bicep isolation exercise with more time under tension to focus on just your biceps short head. It&#8217;s a good finisher to include nearer the end of your workout.</p>



