<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Anatomy Of The Biceps</h2>



<p>Your <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK519538/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">biceps brachii</a> are on the front of your upper arm, between your shoulders and inner forearms. They consist of two main muscle heads: the biceps short head and the biceps long head.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Each head has a slightly different location and function. Therefore, bicep isolation exercises that use different movement patterns can target each head to varying degrees.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The biceps are actually one of the least injured muscles during weight training. Only <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC10689975/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">0.3% of responders</a> reported a bicep injury when training.</p>


